unittitle_ssm: Institute of International Finance Press Clippings
abstract_ssm: The Investment Bankers Association of America, in cooperation with New York University, founded the Institute of International Finance in 1926 as a fact-finding body concerned with foreign economic and financial conditions. This collection contains a scrapbook of press clippings that mention the Institute of International Finance from between 1927 and 1939 and "The Bulletins of NYU's Institute of Finance, 1926-1970: A Review Article," reprinted from the Journal of Economic Literature.
